On the surface of things when you drive past Martha's Place, the exterior is less than thrilling,  but it's the food that we are here for and that's really what counts. Upon entering Martha's Place we were quickly greeted and attended to. The sweet tea was fresh and the ice was cold, so far so good. I ended up ordering a real southern meal or soul food if you like which for me is not an every day thing. What I received was a pleasant surprise. Beef neckbones bursting with flavor   And more than enough beef in a savory gravy/Au jus.  The collar greens were mixed with bacon and as tender as can be and the  savory yellow rice on the side buttery and flavorful.  With corn bread to boot. All that I can say is that it was one of the best meals I've had in years  and the owner and the cook should be proud of themselves. Don't think that this is just a soul food experience they also carry numerous other things on the menu at a more than reasonable price. My dinner was around $10 and it would have rivaled any top restaurant in the international mall area. Give the mom and pop restaurant owners a two thumbs up for Martha's Place and I urge the locals to give it a shot. It is worth it.
